    "INTRODUCTIONS PAM detection has evolved into a critical field of study within cybersecurity, given the exponential growth in electronic communication and its subsequent exploitation by malicious entities [1], [2].",
    "The proliferation of unsolicited bulk messages, or spam, not only poses a nuisance to users but also serves as a vector for more sinister threats such as phishing, malware distribution, and fraud [3], [1].",
    "Effective spam detection mechanisms are essential for protecting users and maintaining the integrity of communication networks.",
    "Traditional approaches have relied heavily on rule-based filters and simple heuristic methods.",
    "However, the adaptive nature of spammers, who continuously evolve their strategies to bypass detection, necessitates more sophisticated and dynamic solutions [1], [4]."
